Not- withstanding this intelligeuce, he began the mass, as usual. During the sacrifice news were brought that the people had got Castulus, an Arian priest, into their hands. S. The Court treated this behaviour as seditious, and imprisoned many of the wealthy tradesmen, and fined them each two hundred pounds of gold.
